RIP Keith Rose — industry reaction and tributes RIP Keith Rose — further industry tributesKeith Rose: Family thanks industry for outpouring of love & tribute by MarkLives. Keith Rose was the director behind some of South Africa's most-iconic television advertising, including BMW's "Mouse" and Allan Gray's "Beautiful", to name only two. Here we include examples of his work, accolades and tributes from social media. In a separate piece, we've collected all tributes which we've received via email in one place. To be added, please send your tribute to 2mark@marklives.com. #AgencyFocus: Grid Worldwide, putting the G in g-forceby Sabrina Forbes. By definition, a grid is a network of wires by which sources of power are distributed, and Grid Worldwide does just that through its unique, design-led work. All the Pendoring 2018 finalistsby MarkLives. Winners of these awards celebrating advertising in indigenous South African languages will be announced at this year’s gala event, scheduled for 1 November 2018 in Joburg. By Invitation Only: Time to embrace change & a shifting creativity business modelby Shukri Toefy & Mikhaila Hunter. A recent announcement by Sir Martin Sorrell acts as an affirmation of a model of a creative, content and production network. #AdForumSummit Amsterdam: Dutch agencies emphasise diversity#AdForumWorldwide Amsterdam: Mix of intl networks, local independents#AdForumSummit Amsterdam: Era of vertical video is now by Johanna McDowell. On Day 1 we met with N=5, Amsterdam Worldwide, Dept, We are Social, and SuperHeroes; on Day 2 it was the turn of MullenLowe, TBWA\NEBOKO, Havas Lemz, The Brave New Now, Reaktor, 72andSunny, and Anomaly; and on Day 3 we saw Ogilvy, Made.For.Digital (which had interesting info on vertical video) and Lemon Scented Tea. Regular Reads Media Design: Avante Garde, Lubalin 100, Sueddeutsche Zeitung, The BarMarket Research Wrap: Major shifts ahead for alcohol bev industrySA TV Ratings: SABC 1 — primetime top 20 for Aug 2018 On the Ra